commit.message: consistent spacing for header #ifndef macros

Double underscores within identifiers are reserved

As double underscores *within* an identifier are reserved,
avoid those in the header file #ifndef macro name.

Also, consistently use comment after header file
trailing #endif:

    #endif /* !defined(EXIF_ACTIONS_H) */

CPP macros beginning/ending with underscores are reserved

C preprocessor macros beginning/ending with underscores are
reserved for system use, so application software macros are
supposed to be named differently.

For a header file foo-bar.h, this consistently uses a macro
name EXIF__FOO_BAR_H for the usual

        #ifndef EXIF__FOO_BAR_H
        #define EXIF__FOO_BAR_H
        ... content of the header file ...
        #endif /* EXIF__FOO_BAR_H */

Found using "clang -Weverything".

This should work, unless when run with an ancient C preprocessor
which might only the first 8 or 10 characters to distinguish
macro names and ignores the remainder of the name.

configure: print the pkg-config program used

Print the pkg-config program used to help with debugging
cross compilation issues.
specify which hexcode the unknown tag has inthe maker note

avoid NULL ptr crash
fixes https://github.com/libexif/exif/issues/5

Update gettext requirement to 0.18.3

gettext 0.18.3 is from 2013-06, which is still earlier than the
2013-12 release date of our other requirement automake 1.14.1.

Amongst other things, this would allow us to use the
AM_XGETTEXT_OPTION macro to add --from-code=UTF-8 to
translate strings written as UTF-8 in *.c source files.

m4m: Remove unused m4m/*.m4 macro files

Remove a number of unused m4m/*.m4 macro files.

The less content in the source tree, the easier it is to
understand.

m4m: Use multi-line EXTRA_DIST for better overview

This should help reading patches and merging.

configure.ac: Move AM_PO_SUBDIRS before AM_GNU_GETTEXT_*

Move AM_PO_SUBDIRS before AM_GNU_GETTEXT_* to avoid error
during the autoreconf run:

  configure.ac:43: error: `po-directories' is already registered with AC_CONFIG_COMMANDS.

configure.ac: Fix indentation of --help output

Reformat the AC_ARG_ENABLE and AS_HELP_STRING invocations
following the AS_HELP_STRING docs.

This fixes the indentation of the --enable-gettext-iconv
description in the output of "configure --help".

configure.ac: Add URL parameter to AC_INIT invocation

Add the URL of the libexif homepage to the AC_INIT invocation.

The resulting AC_PACKAGE_URL m4 macro and PACKAGE_URL sh var
is not used anywhere yet, but it might be useful for
documentation purposes.

The AC_INIT URL parameter is supported since at least
Autoconf version 2.69 which we AC_PREREQ.

configure.ac: Reformat arguments to AC_INIT invocation

Reformat the arguments to the AC_INIT invocation for improved
readability.

There should be no drawbacks with the toolset currently required.
configure.ac: Use m4sh constructs to help with portability

configure.ac: Use multi-line arg for macro calls

Multi-line makes diffs and patches easier to read.

configure.ac: Use AS_HELP_STRING

Use AS_HELP_STRING instead of hard coded messages for
--enable-gettext-iconv.
configure.ac: Consistently use m4 quoting and argument passing

Update autotools requirements and macro use

Update the use of autotools like we just did for libexif:

  * update autoconf and automake version requirements to 2.69 and 1.14.1,
    respectively

  * use LT_INIT instead of obsolete AM_PROG_LIBTOOL

  * generate xz archive when running make dist(check)

  * remove obsolete autoconf macros: AC_C_CONST and AM_PROG_CC_C_O

Equivalent to https://github.com/libexif/libexif/pull/65.
